The Love Aquarium has always been good to my girlfriend and I. They have a wide range of aquatic life and plants. Foods and water treatments that are normally available online (much pricier online)  and never sold at big boxed stores,are available here too. < review>
The Love Aquarium is an awesome local tropical fish store. Employees are definitely down to earth and helpful with any level of aquatic enthusiasts using freshwater aquariums or saltwater aquariums.  I was able to find small fish, chili rasboras, for a tank I have a betta in, with a mix of other sizes of small fish. I have a heavily planted tank for my betta and small fish mix which was spot on recommend by the employees. These guys have more information then your typical big box pet store!  Shop Local!</review>

< user_id>
101566510351192829148</user_id>
<user_name>Tracy Austin<//user_name>< date>
1564858773458< /date>
< Rate>
3<//Rate>
< text>
Two visits and two VERY different experiences.  My first visit would have been rated 5 stars and yesterday's visit one star.  The gentleman that helped me during my first visit was extremely knowledgeable, patient, and so very helpful, even though the shop was heaving with many other patrons.  He even wrote down step-by-step directions on how to set up my tank that was donated to my classroom, tested a pump that was also donated for me, and took all the fake plants from my tank because I wanted to use real plants.  I was so very impressed with the service and expertise of this staff member.  The only piece missing was a particular air stone I wanted that I had to get at another store. I spent $160 on my first visit; a fair and comparable amount of any other store.

I returned a few weeks later with the air stone that I purchased at Pet Co to purchase the tubing (I prefer supporting small businesses) and to buy my fish after having set up my aquarium exactly as the first staff had detailed.  The service I received at this visit was very disappointing.  I had a bag in my hand from Pet Co carrying the air stone to check the size needed for the tubing and this apparently was a trigger for the gentleman. I'm not sure if he was the owner of Love Aquarium or simply a loyal employee.

As per instructions, I was there to buy a few hardy fish to begin the process of introducing necessary bacteria to the tank to then add in GloFish a few weeks later.  I explained what I wanted and this gentlemen started the exchange quite curtly by naming off a few fish without moving to offer much more assistance. I did not have any idea what any of those fish were that he mentioned, so I asked him which ones he would suggest.  Then began a rather frustrating series of exchanges.  He was really unwilling to offer any helpful knowledge beyond which I would have received at Pet Co.

As he was getting my fish in the bag, I asked if I should add the water from the bag to my tank.  He quite rudely told me if I wanted to "seed my water" (not exactly sure what words he suggested here because I wasn't even sure what he meant), that I should "find a friend with an aquarium and get water from them." Still not completely sure where he was headed with this commentary and annoyance with me, I still remained kind and explained I do not have a "friend with an aquarium" and I explained, once again, my purpose with these fish to this gentlemen and again asked if I should or should not pour the water into my tank.  He got very annoyed and said, "You already explained what your plan is." So, I asked again, "Do I add the water?" Here, he revealed why he was perturbed with me, "Not if you're later going to Pet Co to get fish and add their water to the tank."

So, at this point I explained I purchased all my supplies from his store but they did not carry the stone I wanted, but now I was back to get everything else.  His curt response was, "What didn't we have that your wanted?" But really it was a rhetorical question as he walked away and started pulling out additional fish from another tank. I kindly asked what were those fish for (I only wanted the 3 fish he had pulled out just a moment before).  Again, in his ever so polite demeanor explained, "These aren't for you."

Ugh, this guy was a pill.  I remained respectful and patient with him throughout my visit.  He continued to be as little of help as possible.  I spent an additional $60 here yesterday for the fish and some other supplies, but I forgot to buy fish food for my new fishies:(. He just wanted me out of the store.  Sigh. I should also note here that there were only 3-4 families in the shop at this time and there were 2 employees.

So, while I will return for the GloFish in a few weeks, I will NOT be returning to this store for any other purchases.  So very disappointing to show such disrespect to what could have been a loyal customer just because they were carrying a bag from a competitor.<//text>

< userid>
103663881716031669136<//userid>
<Name>Don Nguyen</Name>< time>
1485121241074<//time>
<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
The kids got an empty tank over the holidays and decided to go with a saltwater aquarium. I did some initial research (online) and went to some local pet stores and a specialty store. Never having an aquarium before, I always left every store confused and discouraged. Every person advising me always had a different way of doing things and everyone made it seem like it was a ton of work. Every video online confused me even more.

We came across the Love Aquarium via search and decided to stop in. Doug assured me that it's not complicated and advised me in the most simple of ways. That gave us the confidence we needed. We came back the following day and purchased our live rock, filter, skimmer, substrate, heater, powerhead and enough water to fill a 60 gallon tank. After a day or so of letting the aquarium cycle and clear up, we came back had Doug test our water and the kids picked out their first two fish. We were up and running in less than 3 days.

It's now been 3-4 weeks, we've added another fish, 2 corals, and a nice light for the aquarium. All is running well, and we couldn't be happier!

Doug takes the time to explain everything in detail and is always there to answer every question you have. He always reminds us to bring water in for him to test because he is generally concerned with your success of owning an Aquarium.

There's definitely a family feel to the Love Aquarium. We went into a chain store to look at some stuff since discovering The Love Aquarium and couldn't help but feel guilty being in another store. That said, after seeing the fish at Love Aquarium you realize how unhealthy fish and corals look elsewhere and would never buy from anywhere else.<//text>

I was doing a video vlog with YouTuber Kyle Le and we were shopping around for a betta fish, tank and a few aquatic companions.
After shopping around at PetSmart and Petco, we just couldn't find a good selection of shrimp or healthy snails to be companions to our betta.

The Love Aquarium is located in Escondido, CA  right off the main Valley Parkway, in a small shopping plaza. To be honest, I had to do a Yelp Search for local fish shops to find it. But I‚Äôm SO GLAD that I did!
The Love Aquarium is a hole-in-the-wall shop filled with fishes and well, love! We were helped by a knowledgeable staff that you could just feel their genuine love for aquatic life; this made customer service excellent and friendly.

The staff was patient in answering our inquiries and we didn‚Äôt feel pressured to buy anything. The quality of the fish and their habitats were fantastic and showed that they actively took care of them.
This is the main reason why I will return to The Love Aquarium in the future, because I know that the fishes are genuinely cared for and you don‚Äôt have to fear them being sick when you get one. We ended up finding a lovely wood shrimp for the tank and their prices were reasonable for being a smaller pet shop.

Whether you‚Äôre a tank owner already or looking into being a new pet owner and want to start out small, I‚Äôd recommend getting a fish. I also highly recommend going to The Love Aquarium, because they‚Äôll get you started the right way.

< review>
I would never shop at this live fish store again.  I purchased a $100 naso tang there which died 4 days later.  From the apearnce of the fish it obviously had health issues when I bought it.  When I called the owner he took no responsibility and made no offer of compensation.  He just offered the excuse that the fish must have been "stressed".  I have since purchased a replacement from another source that is doing fine.  I would recommend you don't buy your aquarium fish here.<//review>

*Open for take-out and delivery, also on Grubhub and DoorDash Sept 2020* Servers were wearing masks, but I didn't see any gloves on the cashier.

Oh my goodness where do I begin. I am from Sacramento CA and found myself in the town of Tracy. I came across this place on Yelp and after seeing the great reviews I had to try this place.
I walked inside and was welcomed by no one and a dark room, I thought the place was closed but then a lady appeared and greeted me. < Review>
Dined here on a number of occasions and was very satisfied with my meal.

If you come in for lunch they usually have a selection up from ready which includes their Nan bread which is very good and goes great with whatever you ordered or just plain.

My favorite is their butter chicken over white rice.  The chicken is prepared well and there is enough curry spices to make the meal enjoyable.

This is very good place to dine in but arrive early because of the limited seats available. I  usually order out and eat at home.< /Review>

<text>We ordered few items from menu and it was hit or miss situation. Chiken seekh kabob was okay but hard. Samose were poorly made with potato being bland. <Date>1484267851159< /Date><response>None<//response>< pictures>
None<//pictures>
< username>
Victoria P.<//username>
<rate>4<//rate>< Review>
Dhaba Indian Cuisine has been in Tracy for awhile, and it has been a great addition to the ever growing food scene.  My friends and family come here often whenever we're craving delicious Indian food.

My family and I always get garlic naan, tandoori chicken, and mango lassi.  We switch up the curries now and then, but the chana masala and mango chicken are my favorites.  My parents have been getting the veggie biryani rice, on top of ordering white rice.  The biryani goes well with the tandoori chicken, while I find the white rice doesn't compete with the curries.

The restaurant looks small, but it can accommodate, I would say, two parties of 8 at the same time.  I haven't been to there for lunch, where they offer the food buffet style.  I'd like to do so soon.  I wish Dhaba continued success!<//Review>

Now for the disappointment:  1) One day 5 employees were looking out the window laughing at a homeless man digging in the trash for food. It was really sad. < review>
Leading Edge Plumbing  was recommended to me by a mutual acquaintances (Asif & Laura) . They came over to remove a stoppage. They requested a $69 fee to look at the case, then make a determination. Their determination resulted in them requesting $850 to hydro jet the plumbing and remove the stoppage. I called three companies while I was on the phone with them and got comparable prices. The prices from other companies were much lower. The max price was $600 for the same work and the same warranty. I may be wrong, but It appeared to me that Leading Edge Plumbing  was trying to take advantage of the urgency of the situation. I hired another company , paid not even $400 and the stoppage was taken care off within the hour.<//review>

< text>
Update 09-06-2017: visited again with two friends.  This place has a really unique atmosphere.  I joined my friends in the back on the covered porch because a trivial pursuit game was going on in the front.  My only complaint is the taste of the IPA beer.  I feel like there could be some improvement in the flavors - but this is completely subjective.  Also, they don't serve food except for a nacho chip? platter.  They do allow for pizza delivery although one of the places turned out to be closed on Tuesdays.  A little more organization of the take out food menu like keeping days / times up to date and maybe having all three on a laminated menu card for convenience.

***Again, the atmosphere of the refurbished house alone is worth a visit because there is no place quite like it in San Diego. ***

It's a nice place originally it was a home and it was converted into a business so it has a special feel almost like you're in someone's living room a lot of work went into the decorations and maintaining an antique look one of my favorite things was the bathroom sink is a converted manual selling machine table and the treadle or where you spin it with your foot is still there on top is a galvanized pan with rocks in the bottom and some really cool handles.< /text>

Nicolas Guy< /user_name>

<rating>2<//rating>< Review>
Went in early on a Friday. Bartender/Owner(?) scrutinized my ID and was defensive when I asked him how long this bar had been opened. It didn't help I overheard him stressing out over issues with the city, building, landlord, etc.

They have empty bottles of highly sought after beers next to the beer bottles, which is a little confusing. The tap list features international beer, which is cool, but they have a lot more wine than beer. I overheard the bartender selling a beer to a regular and he was very passionate about it. The info provided to the regular wasn't 100% correct but he was definitely excited about it.

The conversations I had with the bartender were difficult and I would consider it a poor experience. I really like to support small businesses and cute places, but I wouldn't come back. Easy to sell 1 beer, hard to sell 2.</Review>

< text>
We went here to play bingo only to find out that it had been cancelled. That didn't bother us as we liked the atmosphere of the place so we decided to stay for a beer.
The layout of this place was small and cozy. It's a quiant little place to relax and play some board games. There's a modest beer selection and also a wine selection. The staff are friendly but we didn't get a chance to meet the owner as he had just stopped out for the night.
Now the menu here is small and offers only a few things like a meat and cheese plate. Fortunately, there's a BBQ (Ranchwood BBQ) spot right next to them. If you place an order there they will bring it to you in the bar. That's convenient. We didn't get to try the BBQ but it smelled delicious.
If anybody is looking for a quiet little place to unwind and have some wine or beer. This is your spot.<//text>

<Rate>5</Rate><review>Next Door is a local gem and very welcome in an area that sorely needs more great places to hang out. While I generally focus more on their beer selection, I do know that their sangria is very tasty, and they seem very serious about their wine selections. My only complaint on the beer side would be the somewhat slow pace of turnover in the selection from week to week, but this isn't your standard San Diego craft beer bar that blows 3-4 kegs a night. The selection of beer is always good, with a good range of styles to suit most tastes, so this is really a minor issue.

Even though they no longer serve food in the bar, the BBQ place next door, and taco shop down the street make for excellent choices and you are encouraged to bring in outside food, though I do believe Next Door sells the Brother's Provisions cheese plates too.

Don't forget: Tuesday night is trivia night!! We are trivia night regulars and it is always a good time.</review><Pics>None</Pics>< resp>

<date>1590646522263< /date>< review>
Unfortunately, I have to change my review to poor. Today, I had to go to the store because my phone needed a new sim card. When I arrived at 10:15 am the store was already busy. There were only two ATT store associates working. I was told there was a wait of 30 to 45 minutes  because there were 2 people ahead of me and I understood. As time passed more customers started coming in. They put their names on the waitlist and looked for a spot in the store to wait. We were all in the store waiting while keeping social distance. Soon around 11 am another employee came in. All, including myself, felt as if reinforcements had arrived. After being in the back for a few minutes, he came out and asked all the costumers that were waiting in the lobby to step outside to maintain social distancing. I stepped outside with the others, most of which were visibly/and verbally upset about being asked to step outside after waiting so long.

I was not upset about being asked to step outside, due to the current circumstances I understood, what upset me today was that after waiting for an hour the new assoctiate that had arrived was on his phone and playing with the TV they have up for promotion.

I watched him for 15 minutes while he killed time before I approached him to ask how long until they would help me. He said another 25 minutes so I replied, "HOW COME YOU'RE NOT HELPING THE PEOPLE WAITING?" His response, "I'M THE MANAGER AND I HAVE OTHER THINGS TO DO." So I said, "I'M A MANAGER TOO AND IN OUR PERSPECTIVE IT LOOKS WRONG THAT YOU'RE OUT HERE AND NOT HELPING." He replied, "I UNDERSTAND". But still did nothing.

It took another 45 minutes for someone to finally help me since the manager wasn't assisting with customers at all.

While the associate was helping me, I went and asked the manager for his regional manager's email and he said he couldn not give it to me. So I asked for the manager's business card. He then gave me someone else's business card and he handwrote his name on the card with a personal Gmail email address.

I'm assuming that ATT has their own domain for email accounts for their employees and do not use Gmail. The company I work for has it's own email domain. What upsets me is that the person that is supposed to be in charge and help his employees was too lazy or not smart enough to go hide in the back instead of playing with the TV and texting while you have a full store of people that need help. I've been a costumer of ATT for over 10 years and I have never met someone so unprofessional. So to summarize I had to wait 2 hours for a Sim card because the manager couldn't help his associates with the line of customers out the door if he would have helped he could of cut my time in half.</review>
